<p>Recent work in BSSVS 
 <xref rid="pcbi.1000520-Kuo1" ref-type="bibr">[51]</xref>,
 <xref rid="pcbi.1000520-Chipman1" ref-type="bibr">[52]</xref> efficiently performs the exploration in two steps. In the first step, the approach augments the model state-space with a set of 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1000520.e086.jpg" mimetype="image" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula> binary indicator variables 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1000520.e087.jpg" mimetype="image" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula> and imposes a prior 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1000520.e088.jpg" mimetype="image" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula> on the regression coefficients that has expectation 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1000520.e089.jpg" mimetype="image" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula> and variance proportional to a 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1000520.e090.jpg" mimetype="image" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula> diagonal matrix with its entries equal to 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1000520.e091.jpg" mimetype="image" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula>. If 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1000520.e092.jpg" mimetype="image" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula>, then the prior variance on 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1000520.e093.jpg" mimetype="image" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula> shrinks to 0 and enforces 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1000520.e094.jpg" mimetype="image" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula> in the posterior. In the second step, MCMC explores the joint space of 
 <inline-formula>
  <inline-graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1000520.e095.jpg" mimetype="image" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
 </inline-formula> simultaneously.
</p>
